WEBVTT

00:08.125 --> 00:11.295
* Bass, bass, oh
bass, bass *

00:11.328 --> 00:13.998
* Where'd I put my case
for my bass? *

00:14.031 --> 00:16.133
* I have trouble drawing
so I trace

00:16.167 --> 00:17.802
* Oh, oh

00:17.835 --> 00:20.304
* If I lick the amp
will I like the taste? *

00:20.337 --> 00:21.939
* Bass to my face

00:21.973 --> 00:23.174
[ Knock on door ]

00:26.911 --> 00:28.179
Good evening, ma'am.

00:28.212 --> 00:30.715
I just now heard that
a bunch of vampires

00:30.748 --> 00:31.883
came back to -- ooh!

00:31.916 --> 00:34.318
I am the guy
who hunts those guys.

00:34.351 --> 00:37.021
Show me all your vampires.

00:37.054 --> 00:40.291
All the vampires got wiped out,
like, six months ago.

00:40.324 --> 00:42.193
It's just down
to me again.

00:42.226 --> 00:43.961
Really?

00:46.263 --> 00:49.667
I apologize
for the intrusion.

00:49.701 --> 00:51.836
Actually, I'm really glad
you're here.

00:51.869 --> 00:54.238
Hey, BMO,
don't leave yet!

00:54.271 --> 00:56.340
I need your help
with something technical.

00:58.142 --> 00:59.243
Have a sit.

01:01.078 --> 01:04.682
Ta-da!
It's an old USB drive.

01:04.716 --> 01:06.217
I found it in the attic,
and I've been trying

01:06.250 --> 01:09.086
to access it for weeks
using my old hardware.

01:09.120 --> 01:11.889
It's funny, but I can't even
remember what's on it.

01:11.923 --> 01:12.890
Hmm.

01:12.924 --> 01:14.225
I don't know,

01:14.258 --> 01:16.027
maybe you'll
have more luck,

01:16.060 --> 01:19.063
Mr. Vampire Hunter.

01:19.096 --> 01:21.866
I also hunt
data recovery!

01:23.935 --> 01:25.069
Scanning...

01:25.102 --> 01:27.705
[ USB drive humming,
beeping ]

01:30.942 --> 01:32.944
It's going
to be a while.

01:32.977 --> 01:35.346
A while, huh?

01:35.379 --> 01:37.448
Let's use this opportunity
to catch up.

01:37.481 --> 01:39.917
I love ketchup!
Did you make it yourself?

01:39.951 --> 01:41.052
[ Laughs ]

01:41.085 --> 01:42.453
BMO, no.

01:42.486 --> 01:46.423
I mean how was your boat trip
with Finn and Jake?!

01:46.457 --> 01:48.259
Hmm...

01:53.831 --> 01:56.768
Well,
once we left Ooo...

01:56.801 --> 01:59.270
we sailed for 100 days...

01:59.303 --> 02:02.073
until we landed
upon a small island.

02:04.141 --> 02:08.946
We were so tired from sailing,
we decided to take a nap.

02:08.980 --> 02:13.384
Then the island started shaking
and rising from the water.

02:13.417 --> 02:15.953
We were really sleeping
on a big cat

02:15.987 --> 02:20.391
with legs on his back
so he could walk upside down.

02:20.424 --> 02:23.060
What's going on here?

02:23.094 --> 02:25.362
He said his name was Ted.

02:25.396 --> 02:27.098
My name is Ted.

02:27.131 --> 02:31.803
Whoaaaaaaaa!

02:31.836 --> 02:34.471
A big blue jay
was making noise nearby.

02:34.505 --> 02:37.074
Whoaaaa!

02:37.108 --> 02:38.943
So we walked somewhere else.

02:38.976 --> 02:41.445
Whoa!
Oh!

02:41.478 --> 02:43.547
Whoa!
Whoa!

02:43.580 --> 02:46.417
We saw some boats
in the clouds.

02:46.450 --> 02:49.086
Finn sang a song,
even though he was asleep.

02:49.120 --> 02:51.856
* I want to ride on
a boat, boat, boat *

02:51.889 --> 02:54.425
* I want to ride on
a goat, goat, goat *

02:54.458 --> 02:57.328
* Middle C is my favorite
note, note, note *

02:57.361 --> 03:00.164
* I'm on a cat
that floats, floats, floats *

03:00.197 --> 03:02.333
Then we floated
with the boats --

03:02.366 --> 03:05.136
not in the boats,
but with the boats.

03:05.169 --> 03:07.839
And we disappeared
into the clouds.

03:09.506 --> 03:11.442
That's how I remember it,

03:11.475 --> 03:13.344
though I might
have embellished.

03:13.377 --> 03:17.248
So, what did you do
while i was on my trip?

03:17.281 --> 03:18.482
Huh?

03:18.515 --> 03:20.885
That was awesome,
BMO.

03:20.918 --> 03:23.587
What are you making?

03:23.620 --> 03:25.289
Puppets!

03:25.322 --> 03:27.191
Oh, my blogs!

03:27.224 --> 03:29.961
You are going to catch me up
with a puppet story?

03:29.994 --> 03:33.130
Yup!
You gave me the idea!

03:33.164 --> 03:35.166
I'm so happy
right now!

03:37.935 --> 03:40.872
I'll try to make it
interesting -- the BMO way.

03:42.539 --> 03:45.076
Once there was this...

03:45.109 --> 03:46.610
lollipop girl.

03:46.643 --> 03:48.545
Princess Bubblegum?

03:48.579 --> 03:51.515
So there was
this lollipop girl.

03:51.548 --> 03:54.085
She was really sweet...

03:54.118 --> 03:56.320
and really smart.

03:56.353 --> 03:58.355
Her best friend was...

03:58.389 --> 04:00.191
rock star girl.

04:00.224 --> 04:01.625
[ Guitar strums ]

04:01.658 --> 04:02.994
'Nuff said.

04:03.027 --> 04:04.328
They were pretty different,

04:04.361 --> 04:06.898
but they grokked each other.

04:06.931 --> 04:09.033
They lived on
a giant birthday cake

04:09.066 --> 04:13.004
called Weekend City,
where clocks were illegal

04:13.037 --> 04:15.539
and everyone
was chill as heck.

04:15.572 --> 04:17.942
[ Horn toots ]
Ha ha! Hey!

04:17.975 --> 04:19.443
Ha ha!
Hey!

04:19.476 --> 04:22.346
* You don't need a pill
to be chill *

04:22.379 --> 04:24.248
* Just have a dill pickle

04:24.281 --> 04:25.883
* Go get tickled

04:25.917 --> 04:27.952
* And do not kill

04:27.985 --> 04:30.354
Hey, my page!

04:30.387 --> 04:34.091
* I'm gonna go pee

04:34.125 --> 04:36.127
* Sorry

04:38.629 --> 04:42.900
But one day, a mysterious,
cold fart

04:42.934 --> 04:46.403
brought the evil blue tranch
into town.

04:46.437 --> 04:49.073
Ha-ha!

04:49.106 --> 04:51.275
Hey, there!

04:51.308 --> 04:53.244
Hi. You seem like you'd be into
fulfilling

04:53.277 --> 04:55.947
your evolutionary potential
by becoming a potato-head.

04:55.980 --> 04:58.449
Am I right
or am I right?

04:58.482 --> 05:01.252
Remember that clocks were
illegal in Weekend City.

05:01.285 --> 05:03.120
Well,
today's your lucky day...

05:03.154 --> 05:06.457
'cause I'm offering
this magic fertilizer.

05:06.490 --> 05:08.325
Whoo!

05:08.359 --> 05:11.128
Marceline: Lollipop girl
turned her down cold.

05:11.162 --> 05:13.230
[ Growls ] I'll never get
these normies

05:13.264 --> 05:15.266
to understand
what they're missing.

05:15.299 --> 05:17.168
To be pure potato.

05:17.201 --> 05:19.636
Pure tato.

05:19.670 --> 05:23.941
Marceline: And so, unwilling
to give up her bad plan...

05:23.975 --> 05:27.344
[ Laughing ]

05:27.378 --> 05:29.981
Marceline: The blue tranch
crop-dusted the whole town,
[ Cloud farts ]

05:30.014 --> 05:32.416
turning everyone
into potato-heads!

05:32.449 --> 05:34.418
[ Coughing ]

05:36.620 --> 05:38.255
Huh?
[ Sniffs ]

05:38.289 --> 05:40.992
Ew!
[ Screams ]

05:41.025 --> 05:44.495
Marceline: But lollipop girl
got it the worst.

05:44.528 --> 05:48.699
Her potato was growing potatoes
on potatoes.

05:48.732 --> 05:52.003
She was turning into a full-on
potato-stack --

05:52.036 --> 05:54.972
and I mean crazy tall.

05:55.006 --> 05:57.041
How tall?

05:57.074 --> 06:00.344
Mmm...
12 giants tall.

06:00.377 --> 06:04.181
Oh! That is even taller
than when PB got tall.

06:04.215 --> 06:06.017
[ Clears throat ]

06:06.050 --> 06:08.019
Anyways...

06:08.052 --> 06:10.221
Rock star girl was tough.

06:10.254 --> 06:12.323
She fought back the curse.

06:12.356 --> 06:14.625
**

06:19.030 --> 06:22.066
She promised lollipop girl
she would save her.

06:26.570 --> 06:30.374
She travelled all the way
to Potato Town

06:30.407 --> 06:33.010
to confront the blue tranch.

06:33.044 --> 06:34.545
[ Screams ]

06:34.578 --> 06:37.081
* Hey, Blue Tranch
I'll give you one chance *

06:37.114 --> 06:39.583
* To fix my friend
Or I'll kick your pants *

06:39.616 --> 06:42.319
* La la la la
la la la la *

06:42.353 --> 06:44.455
* La la la la
la la la la *

06:44.488 --> 06:46.557
Stop!

06:46.590 --> 06:48.325
I have migraines!

06:50.527 --> 06:52.229
It turned out
the blue tranch's head

06:52.263 --> 06:54.731
was too dense
to appreciate good music.

06:54.765 --> 06:57.368
So rock star girl kicked
her pants with songs.

06:57.401 --> 07:00.104
* Kicks, kicks, kicks
Take that and take this *

07:00.137 --> 07:03.340
Until, finally,
the tranch gave up the antidote.

07:03.374 --> 07:05.276
There!
Are you happy now?!

07:06.710 --> 07:10.247
Yes!
You go, rock star girl!

07:10.281 --> 07:12.483
But now it gets sad.

07:12.516 --> 07:14.385
Oh, no.
Why?

07:14.418 --> 07:15.586
Well...

07:15.619 --> 07:17.421
Rock star girl
wasn't really sure

07:17.454 --> 07:19.523
if the blue tranch gave her
the real antidote...

07:19.556 --> 07:22.293
or if it was just a trick
to get rid of her.

07:22.326 --> 07:25.562
But the potato curse
had started to spread faster,

07:25.596 --> 07:28.132
so it was kind
of her only shot.

07:29.633 --> 07:32.103
Rock star girl used her last
bit of strength

07:32.136 --> 07:34.738
to climb the potato stalk.

07:34.771 --> 07:38.209
But when she finally reached
the top, she discovered...

07:38.242 --> 07:39.276
[ Gasps ]

07:39.310 --> 07:40.444
That lollipop girl

07:40.477 --> 07:43.280
was a completely
different person.

07:43.314 --> 07:46.083
Ha, ha!
No!

07:46.117 --> 07:48.285
Rock star girl
was heart-broken.

07:48.319 --> 07:50.787
All she'd wanted was to have
her best friend back,

07:50.821 --> 07:53.290
but she was gone.

07:53.324 --> 07:56.660
As the potato curse consumed
her final thoughts,

07:56.693 --> 07:59.230
she decided to
embrace her fate...

07:59.263 --> 08:02.566
to -- to explode
into stardust!

08:02.599 --> 08:04.201
[ Strums guitar ]

08:05.636 --> 08:07.604
The end.

08:07.638 --> 08:10.107
What?!
Okay.

08:10.141 --> 08:12.309
But she was you,
right?

08:12.343 --> 08:15.312
If that's how
you interpreted it.

08:15.346 --> 08:16.613
That ending...

08:16.647 --> 08:18.449
was not believable.

08:18.482 --> 08:21.485
Come on. You had a cat
with legs on its back.

08:21.518 --> 08:24.488
I was being emotionally
truthful.

08:24.521 --> 08:27.591
Fine.
I sort of copped out.

08:27.624 --> 08:31.162
I guess I just got some stuff
that's harder to talk about.

08:31.195 --> 08:34.665
Maybe 'cause I never actually
talked about it for real --

08:34.698 --> 08:36.267
not even to myself.

08:36.300 --> 08:37.634
[ Bell dings ]

08:37.668 --> 08:39.270
Pancakes are ready!

08:39.303 --> 08:40.471
Oh.

08:40.504 --> 08:42.406
[ Whirs ]

08:42.439 --> 08:43.507
Burp.

08:43.540 --> 08:45.142
So what's on
the drive?

08:45.176 --> 08:47.478
I will show you.

08:47.511 --> 08:50.113
**

08:55.886 --> 08:58.489
[ Gasps ]
BMO, pause slide show!

09:06.563 --> 09:08.665
Mom.

09:11.335 --> 09:13.204
Marceline?

09:13.237 --> 09:16.307
Who's the nice lady
and the little girl?

09:16.340 --> 09:19.510
It's um...

09:19.543 --> 09:20.744
I don't know, Beems.

09:20.777 --> 09:22.313
Why don't you tell me
a story

09:22.346 --> 09:24.315
about the little girl
and the nice lady.

09:24.348 --> 09:25.816
Okay!

09:25.849 --> 09:28.752
Once there was a lady
who lived in the moon.

09:31.422 --> 09:35.226
She was called Moon Lady,
and she could only come out

09:35.259 --> 09:37.894
during lunar eclipses.

09:37.928 --> 09:42.699
Once there was a little girl
playing alone by the sea.

09:42.733 --> 09:44.668
"Hello,
little girl."

09:44.701 --> 09:46.203
"Who are you?"

09:46.237 --> 09:50.407
"I'm the moon lady,"
said the Moon Lady.

09:50.441 --> 09:52.576
They became best friends.

09:54.278 --> 09:57.214
They swam in
the dirty ocean water,

09:57.248 --> 10:00.351
rolled down a hill
on a giant beach ball,

10:00.384 --> 10:03.920
played
"can you catch me?"

10:03.954 --> 10:06.590
And rode horses
or something.

10:06.623 --> 10:08.692
They had so much fun.

10:08.725 --> 10:11.728
But, soon, the eclipse
started to vanish...

10:11.762 --> 10:14.465
and the moon lady
had to say good-bye...

10:14.498 --> 10:17.734
because eclipses
can't last forever.

10:17.768 --> 10:21.305
But the little girl
never forgot the moon lady.

10:23.307 --> 10:25.776
Or their friendship.

10:25.809 --> 10:28.479
I think I've heard
a story like that...

10:28.512 --> 10:31.282
a long,
long time ago.

10:31.315 --> 10:33.250
[ Sniffles ]

10:33.284 --> 10:34.951
That was beautiful,
BMO.

10:34.985 --> 10:38.589
Well,
it's a beautiful picture.

10:38.622 --> 10:39.723
The end.

10:40.824 --> 10:41.925
[ Upbeat music plays ]

10:41.958 --> 10:45.896
Come along with me

10:45.929 --> 10:49.900
And the butterflies and bees

10:53.370 --> 10:55.606
This party is so crazy!
